<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Centaurea</i> <i>calcitrapa</i>, <i>Centaurea</i> <i>virgata</i> ssp. <i>squarrosa</i> or another knapweed species is dominant or co-dominant with other non-natives in the herbaceous layer. Emergent trees and shrubs may be present at low cover. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 1.5 m; cover is intermittent to continuous. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Open disturbed sites, roadsides, upland grasslands, moist meadows, rangeland, and open hillsides.  </div>
</div>

		
